<plot>With his sister stuck in the Christmas tree like an ornament, the Angry Kid sits on the family couch, wearing white gloves and a small crown. He's preparing to tape the Queen's annual Christmas message as 1999 comes to a close. It takes more than one take for the Kid to discard his usual demeanor for that of the Monarch: "As we leave the old millennium..." But even then, can he pull off the entire script, or will the director have to call central casting?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?451449</url></doc>
